Key Match Events: Cameron Johnson was fouled by Tatum after missing a wide open 3-point attempt in the closing seconds of regulation but grabbed his own miss. He calmly sank two free throws, tying it at 94 with 7.6 seconds to play.
Tatum front-rimmed a 3 as time expired, sending it to OT.
Boston forced the Nets into a shot-clock violation before Pritchard was fouled on the other end and hit two free throws.
Pre-Game Insights: Coach Jordi Fernandez talked before the game that it was going to be ‘exciting because they like to run, too,’ so they slowed Boston by picking up defensively deep in the backcourt most of the game.
Post-Match Reflections: The Celtics were held below its league-leading average of 19 3-pointers made per game. They ended up shooting 14 for 53 from deep, but the Nets only made 10 3s.
